</p>
<p>And maybe that's enough for you. But, if you <em>do</em> need the ability to assign different
permissions to different users, then we've gotta go a little further.</p>
<p>Let's say that in <em>our</em> system, we're going to give different users different roles.
How do we do that? Simple! Just create a <code>private $roles</code> property that's an array.
Give it the <code>@ORM\Column</code> annotation and set its type to <code>json_array</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="11cb890ee2">
