</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p><code>json_array</code> type is deprecated since Doctrine 2.6, you should use <code>json</code> instead.</p>
</div><p>This is <em>really</em> cool because the <code>$roles</code> property will hold an <em>array</em> of roles,
but when we save, Doctrine will automatically <code>json_encode</code> that array and store
it in a <em>single</em> field. When we query, it'll <code>json_decode</code> that back to the array.
What this means is that we can store an array inside a single column, without ever
worrying about the JSON encode stuff.</p>
<h2 id="returning-the-dynamic-roles">Returning the Dynamic Roles <a class="headerlink" href="dynamic-roles#returning-the-dynamic-roles" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
