	                                <p>Hmm. I was used to roles and permissions structure. I mean, used to have a roles table, permissions table, pivot tables between them, user could have roles but also a independent permissions and so on. I was using <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fromanbican%2Froles%3AfzP2DANrZwj2FEy4q8MCL6UFY5s&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/romanbican/...</a> with Laravel.</p><p>How this relates to Symfony? Do groups act as roles and roles become permissions in Symfony world? If a role represents a set of permissions, hard coded in my application (according to: <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fstackoverflow.com%2Fquestions%2F8848156%2Fwhat-is-the-difference-between-acl-and-user-roles-in-symfony2%3AKqcPYZdbNICDzHomSFg8l1TF3tc&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">http://stackoverflow.com/quest...</a> ) how am I supposed to associate permissions with roles?</p>
